Sao Martinho SA (SMTO3)  is among three
sugar-cane processors that will get a total of 356.2 million
reais ($158.6 million) from  Brazil â€™s development bank to help
plant crops.  The companies will replant sugar cane in 71,500 hectares
(176,680 acres) and plant the crop in 11,700 hectares of new
fields, Rio de Janeiro-based Banco Nacional de Desenvolvimento
Economico & Social said in an e-mail today.  Sao Martinho will receive 65.1 million reais to plant crops
in Sao Paulo state and Usina de Acucar Santa Terezinha Ltda.
will get 253.2 million reais to boost feedstock for two mills in
Parana state, according to the statement.  Cia. Agricola Quata, a unit of Zilor Group, will get 37.9
million reais for work in  Sao Paulo , BNDES said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
